14494254,-0.03455044,-0.03627164,0.02431731,0.04629698,-0.02273042,0.00651633,0.04123345,0.04407011,0.02561270,0.04226424,-0.02724746,0.01569149,-0.07869441,0.00138132,0.07338860,-0.05847466,0.01735301,-0.02987786,0.01196054,-0.00801886,-0.03015565,0.03641906,0.01011596,-0.02864632,-0.12423321,-0.08752275,0.09843156,-0.01766965,-0.09122632,0.02334432,-0.05377016,0.09158370,-0.03689565,0.00402967,0.01524839,-0.04967272,0.07922179,0.07368422,0.02275457,0.07053834,0.02511753,-0.00029746]',E'Middleware { #middleware }\n\nYou can add middleware to **FastAPI** applications.\n\nA "middleware" is a function that works with every **request** before it is processed by any specific *path operation*. And also with every **response** before returning it.\n\n* It takes each **request** that comes to your application.\n* It can then do something to that **request** or run any needed code.\n* Then it passes the **request** to be processed by the rest of the application (by some *path operation*).\n* It then takes the **response** generated by the application (by some *path operation*).\n* It can do something to that **response** or run any needed code.\n* Then it returns the **response**.\n\n/// note | Technical Details\n\nIf you have dependencies with `yield`, the exit code will run *after* the middleware.\n\nIf there were any background tasks (covered in the [Background Tasks](background-tasks.md) section, you will see it later), they will run *after* all the middleware.\n\n///','{"source": "fastapi", "version": "0.136", "language": "python", "title": "Middleware { #middleware }", "section_title": "middleware", "url": "https://github.com/fastapi/fastapi/blob/master/docs/en/docs/tutorial/middleware.md", "topics": "fastapi,async,middleware", "categories": "web,python,rest,async"}');
