4,0.09074050,0.05584039,0.01231043,0.06558958,0.08189209,0.03184760,0.03597528,0.02620507,-0.01509717,0.00349909,0.07599301,-0.03689964,-0.00796274,0.00623935,-0.00660522,-0.02804197,-0.00700003,0.00861960,-0.00730197,0.03701524,0.03529787,0.02916371,0.03217336,-0.00314871,0.02766145,-0.08405275,-0.05217466,0.00056034,0.00419206,-0.03299525,0.01995995,0.00036707,0.07438996,-0.00574517,0.04100922,0.04144241,0.01181349,0.05668712,0.01201252,0.01637542,0.06049615,0.03302046,-0.06390017]',E'Create a Session Dependency { #create-a-session-dependency }\n\nA **`Session`** is what stores the **objects in memory** and keeps track of any changes needed in the data, then it **uses the `engine`** to communicate with the database.\n\nWe will create a FastAPI **dependency** with `yield` that will provide a new `Session` for each request. This is what ensures that we use a single session per request. 🤓\n\nThen we create an `Annotated` dependency `SessionDep` to simplify the rest of the code that will use this dependency.\n\n{* ../../docs_src/sql_databases/tutorial001_an_py310.py ln[25:30]  hl[25:27,30] *}','{"source": "fastapi", "version": "0.136", "language": "python", "title": "SQL (Relational) Databases { #sql-relational-databases }", "section_title": "sql-databases", "url": "https://github.com/fastapi/fastapi/blob/master/docs/en/docs/tutorial/sql-databases.md", "topics": "fastapi,async,sql,databases", "categories": "web,python,rest,async"}');
