68,0.12814720,-0.00363113,0.02870563,-0.03186358,0.03664060,-0.09860614,0.04526084,-0.00998139,0.04476392,-0.02530576,0.10712884,-0.00182023,-0.01745479,-0.02684971,-0.00342509,0.00572789,-0.02215967,0.01941858,0.03620686,0.03993855,-0.07505527,0.00811876,0.05044551,-0.00550507,-0.00886079,-0.08675513,-0.03554970,0.03879831,0.02981802,-0.02276898,0.01723475,-0.02342648,0.04052422,-0.02570544,0.00699293,0.04033856,-0.03624234,0.06763906,0.07971451,0.00546385,0.00426424,0.10083658,0.03827202]',E'Return Type and Data Filtering { #return-type-and-data-filtering }\n\nAnd in those cases, we can use classes and inheritance to take advantage of function **type annotations** to get better support in the editor and tools, and still get the FastAPI **data filtering**.\n\n{* ../../docs_src/response_model/tutorial003_01_py310.py hl[7:10,13:14,18] *}\n\nWith this, we get tooling support, from editors and mypy as this code is correct in terms of types, but we also get the data filtering from FastAPI.\n\nHow does this work? Let''s check that out. 🤓','{"source": "fastapi", "version": "0.136", "language": "python", "title": "Response Model - Return Type { #response-model-return-type }", "section_title": "response-model", "url": "https://github.com/fastapi/fastapi/blob/master/docs/en/docs/tutorial/response-model.md", "topics": "fastapi,async,response,model", "categories": "web,python,rest,async"}');
